BFN 

  [Text] His Highness the Amir received at 0900 Shaykh Sa'd 
al-'Abdallah al-Salim al-Sabah, heir apparent and prime minister 
who presented the ministers appointed in the latest cabinet 
reshuffle. 
  Defense Minister Ahmad al-Hamud al-Jabir al-Sabah; Ahmad 
Khalid al-Kulayb, social affairs and labor minister; Habib 
Jawhar Hayat, minister of public works and housing minister of 
state; Jasim Muhammad al-'Awn, minister of communications, 
electricity, and water; 'Abd al-'Aziz Dakhil al-Dakhil, planning 
minister and minister of state for cabinet affairs; Oil Minister 
Dr. 'Abd al- Muhsin Mid'aj al-Mid'aj; Interior Minister 'Ali 
Sabah al-Salim al- Sabah; Health Minister Dr. 'Abd al-Rahman 
Salih al-Muhaylan; Dr. 'Ali Fahd al-Zumay', minister of 
religious endowments and Islamic affairs; and Hilal Mishari 
al-Mutayri, minister of commerce and industry, all made the 
constitutional oath to His Highness the Amir, to mark their 
appointments in their new posts. 

